sentences.english: Some of them are spaceships from outer space.
sentences.chinese: 有些不明飛行物是外太空來訪的太空船。

sentences.english: Fear and greed expose the spaceship crew to an alien  parasite.
sentences.chinese: 恐懼和貪婪使太空船成員受到外星寄生蟲的威脅。

sentences.english: The spaceship named pluto no. 4 will be launched by the united states .
sentences.chinese: 太空船布魯特四號將由美國發射升空。

sentences.english: My husband and I live near Spaceport .
sentences.chinese: 我和我丈夫住在太空船發射降落場附近。

sentences.english: How is the space shuttle better than rockets or spaceships?
sentences.chinese: 太空穿梭機比起火箭或太空船有什麼優點？

sentences.english: Some people were convinced that crop circles were sites where alien spaceships had landed.
sentences.chinese: 有些人深信麥田圈是外星人太空船所降落的地方。

sentences.english: How do you power a spacecraft in deep space?
sentences.chinese: 進入深空，我們如何驅動太空船？

sentences.english: For the little spacecraft that could, there is no rest. Galileo goes on, to Ganymede.
sentences.chinese: 這艘小太空船，伽利略號片刻未停繼續前往蓋尼米德。

sentences.english: Our Autobot space craft has the ability to get there.
sentences.chinese: 我們博派的太空船有能力到那裏。

sentences.english: Why is this news…even Japan has launched space missions.
sentences.chinese: 這新聞有啥意思？倭寇早就發射太空船了。

sentences.english: In science class we talked about robots and spaceships .
sentences.chinese: 在科學課我們討論了機器人和太空船。

sentences.english: Travel between consensus realities did not require spacecraft or spacesuits.
sentences.chinese: 一致實相間的旅行並不需要太空船或太空服。
兩艘太空船成功地會合。

sentences.english: The spacecraft was fitted with a heat-shield.
sentences.chinese: 太空船裝置了防熱護罩。

sentences.english: The launch is the first stage in the key Cluster II programme.
sentences.chinese: 這次發射是“星羣二號”太空船計劃的實施第一步。

sentences.english: Abraham blocks the advance at the gateway to the Spaceport.
sentences.chinese: 亞伯拉罕的軍隊在太空船發射降落場的通路前進。

definition: moon landing/to land on the moon
Star Trek (US TV and film series)
